    {
      "id": "92c45382_f533fc43",
      "file_path": "plans/ccsdk-oran/polmansuite/test_env.sh",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 33,
      "message": "From what I understood now after some investigation is that snapshot should be used for CSIT as snapshot images are built after merge. Staging is a release candidate and I guess they are built less often - so not ideal for CSIT. I guess the SDNC does not have snapshot because it is built from many different components? \nSo based on the investigation I will use snapshot/staging image tags like below:\nPOLICY_AGENT_REMOTE_IMAGE_TAG=\"1.1.0-SNAPSHOT\"\nSDNC_A1_CONTROLLER_REMOTE_IMAGE_TAG=\"2.1.0-STAGING-latest\"",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5074,
        "name": "Bjorn Magnusson",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "konsultbjorn@yahoo.se",
        "username": "BjornMagnussonXA"
      },
      "updated": "2020-09-17 12:20:37.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "ac8718f7_6a0eb65f",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "2888092b_4a9e0da3",
      "file_path": "plans/ccsdk-oran/polmansuite/test_env.sh",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 50,
      "message": "Cleaned out all vars starting with SDNC_ONAP* in the test_env.sh.\nThe test environment was initially intended to have the possibility to configure two different SDNC images with different start commands (start_sndc and start_sdnc_onap) and also two sets of vars. This never came into real use but kept for possible future use. \n\nThe start cmd start_sdnc_onap and related functions in the test environment will be removed when refactoring the test environment.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5074,
        "name": "Bjorn Magnusson",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "konsultbjorn@yahoo.se",
        "username": "BjornMagnussonXA"
      },
      "updated": "2020-09-17 12:20:37.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "b381e032_dafe007b",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
